---
title: Egg-In-A-Hole BLT on Whole Wheat Bread with a Side Salad
description: Do you like BLTs? Of course you do—who doesn’t smile at the sight of bacon? What about eggs? Yep, we thought so. Now what if we told you that we combined the two in the most adorable way? Ohhh yeah! In this recipe, bacon, lettuce, and tomato are layered onto whole wheat bread, then topped with another slice that’s got an egg inside its cut-out center. Get your cameras ready, because you’ll want to show off your #breakfastgoals to all your friends.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/egg-in-a-hole-blt-d371fd9e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/egg-in-a-hole-blt-b91bfb91.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/egg-in-a-hole-blt-59838028043c3c281d2b9253
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 62 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1000 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Add @bacon{4%ounce} to a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook to desired
doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Set aside on a #paper towel{} to drain.
Drain and discard any grease from pan, then wipe out with another paper towel.

Wash and dry all produce. Core @roma tomatoes{2}(sliced into ¼-inch-thick
rounds). Trim root end from @romaine lettuce{1}. Set aside 2 large leaves for
sandwiches. Roughly chop remainder into bite-sized pieces. Halve @lemon{1} then
cut one half into wedges. Cut out a hole from the centers of 2
@whole wheat bread{4} slices using a #small glass{} or #can{}.

Stir together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and 1 tsp @italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}
in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add 2 uncut
bread slices and toast until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Remove from
pan and set aside. Add another 1 TBSP butter and a large drizzle of
@vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} to pan. Place cut bread slices in pan. Carefully
crack an @eggs{2} into each hole. Cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Toss together chopped lettuce, half the seasoned mayonnaise, a drizzle of oil,
and a squeeze of lemon in a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread remaining seasoned mayo onto one side of each uncut bread slice. Top with
bacon, lettuce leaves, and a few tomato slices. Place egg-filled bread slices on
top. Toss any remaining tomato into salad. Serve sandwiches with salad on the
side and any remaining lemon for squeezing over.